text: The 9th District of the Iowa Senate is located in southwestern Iowa, and is currently composed of Crawford, Harrison, Ida, Monona, Shelby, and Woodbury Counties. ==Current elected officials== Jason Schultz is the senator currently representing the 9th District. The area of the 9th District contains two Iowa House of Representatives districts: *The 17th District (represented by Matt Windschitl) *The 18th District (represented by Steven Holt) The district is also located in Iowa's 4th congressional district, which is represented by U.S. Representative Steve King. ==Past senators== The district has previously been represented by: *Dale L. Tieden, 1981-1982 *Ray Taylor, 1983-1994 *Stewart Iverson J, 1995-2002 *Bob Brunkhorst, 2003-2006 *Bill Heckroth, 2007-2010 *Bill Dix, 2011-2012 *Nancy Boettger, 2013-2014 *Jason Schultz, 2015-present ==See also== *Iowa General Assembly *Iowa Senate ==References== 09
title: Iowa Senate, District 9
